Moonraker
Copyright (c) 2026 Real-Fruit-Snacks

This product is a Lua port of Mainsail
(https://github.com/Real-Fruit-Snacks/Mainsail), an MIT-licensed
BusyBox-style multi-call utility binary. Behavior, applet inventory, and
test parity track Mainsail upstream.

Vendored third-party components (under src/vendor/ and src/cdeps/) carry
their own licenses; see each component's LICENSE file for details.

scripts/luastatic.lua is a vendored copy of luastatic 0.0.12
(https://github.com/ers35/luastatic). The upstream author placed the
source in the public domain. We carry a small Windows-portability patch
(see the file header for details). Re-vendor by copying the upstream
file and re-applying the patch.

src/cdeps/lpeg/ contains LPeg 1.1.0 by Roberto Ierusalimschy, copyright
2007-2023 Lua.org & PUC-Rio, distributed under the MIT/X11 license.
Upstream: https://www.inf.puc-rio.br/~roberto/lpeg.html. See
src/cdeps/lpeg/LICENSE for the full text. The C sources are compiled
unmodified and linked into the moonraker binary; `require("lpeg")`
inside the binary resolves to this embedded module.

src/vendor/re.lua is the re.lua frontend that ships with LPeg 1.1.0,
unmodified. `require("vendor.re")` (or, for users with system LPeg
installed, `require("re")`) returns the regex-style PEG compiler.

src/vendor/sha2.lua is Egor Skriptunoff's pure_lua_SHA v12, MIT-licensed,
copyright (c) Egor Skriptunoff. Upstream:
https://github.com/Egor-Skriptunoff/pure_lua_SHA. Single-file pure-Lua
implementation of MD5/SHA-1/SHA-2/SHA-3/HMAC. Backs the *sum applets.

src/cdeps/zlib/ contains zlib 1.3.1 by Jean-loup Gailly and Mark Adler
(zlib license, 1995-2024). Upstream: https://zlib.net/. Compiled with
-DLZLIB_COMPAT (via src/cdeps/zlib/cflags) so the lua-zlib glue exposes
its compatibility constants. See src/cdeps/zlib/LICENSE.zlib.

src/cdeps/zlib/lua_zlib.c is the lua-zlib 1.4-0 binding by Brian Maher
(MIT license, copyright 2009-2024). Provides the `zlib` Lua module
backed by zlib above. Backs the gzip / gunzip / tar -z applets.

src/cdeps/luasocket/ contains LuaSocket 3.1.0 by Diego Nehab
(MIT license, copyright 2004-2022). Upstream:
https://github.com/lunarmodules/luasocket. We vendor only the POSIX
TCP/UDP/select C sources (auxiliar, buffer, compat, except, inet, io,
luasocket, options, select, tcp, timeout, udp, usocket) and the
top-level socket.lua helper module. The mime, ftp, http, smtp, and
unix-socket modules are intentionally not vendored — `http` shells out
to curl/wget for HTTPS, and `nc`/`dig` need only raw sockets. See
src/cdeps/luasocket/LICENSE.

src/socket.lua is LuaSocket's socket.lua helper from the same upstream,
placed at the top level so `require("socket")` resolves cleanly under
luastatic's path-derived module-name scheme.

src/cdeps/bzip2/ contains bzip2 1.0.8 by Julian Seward
(BSD-style license, copyright 1996-2019). Upstream:
https://sourceware.org/bzip2/. We vendor only the library sources
(blocksort, bzlib, compress, crctable, decompress, huffman, randtable
and the headers). The `bzip2` / `bunzip2` / `bzip2recover` CLI tools
are intentionally not vendored — moonraker users `tar -j` for the
common-case (tarball compression). See src/cdeps/bzip2/LICENSE.

src/cdeps/bzip2/lua_bzip2.c is moonraker's own minimal Lua binding
to libbzip2: a one-shot `bzip2.compress(data, level)` /
`bzip2.decompress(data)` API used by `tar -j`. Same MIT license as
the rest of moonraker.
